    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Issue 1 - Watchdog Reset in application Information Analysis Solution Fix Status Issue 2 - Stuck in Bootloader Information Analysis Solution Fix Status"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "DET means Development Error Tracer in Autosar 4.0 and is renamed to Default Error Tracer in Autosar 4.2."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "DET provides functionality to support error detection and tracing of errors during the development of Software Components and other Basic Software Modules. For this purpose DET receives and evaluates error messages from these components and modules. DET is able to provide information need for tracing source and kind of error."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Issue 1 - Watchdog Reset in application"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Information"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Found in Project",
        "GWM V3.5",
        "RTC Ticket",
        ""
      ],
      "rows": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Analysis"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "During development,  once anerror is reported via Det_ReportError interface, the system will enter to endless loop via Det_EndlessLoop interface."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "After that, the software can not trigger watchdog and this will result watchdog timeout, finally the system will reset by the HW watchdog."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Solution"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Normally, the DET functionality shall be disabled after SOP, which means the system will not enter to endless loop."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "But with this change, some important error information will be lost."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "After checked with Vector, it is possible to remove Det_EndlessLoop when issue happened, and it is also possible to store the error information in Det_callouts."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "More detail information can be found in slides."
    },
    {
